  "title": "Kinetic energy - analyzing position vs time graph",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a graph of 2 connected line segments in a 4 by 2 gridded plane. The horizontal axis is labeled t, and the numbers 0 through 8, in increments of 2, are indicated. The vertical axis is labeled x and the numbers 0 through 2, in increments of 1, are indicated. The first line segment begins at coordinates 0 comma 1.5 and moves downward and to the right to coordinates 4 comma 1. The second line segment begins at coordinates 4 comma 1 and moves downward and to the right to coordinates 6 comma 0.\" src=\"/images/201b5b2b3d5862b1bacb97cb252af383.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">An object moves along a horizontal surface in a straight line and its position as a function of time is shown in the graph. Which of the following statements best describes the kinetic energy of the object for the time interval shown in the graph?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i2",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The kinetic energy of the object decreases uniformly for the first <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4\"><math alttext=\"4\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>4</mn></math></span></span> seconds, then decreases uniformly at a higher rate for the next <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> seconds.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The kinetic energy of the object remains constant for the first <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4\"><math alttext=\"4\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>4</mn></math></span></span> seconds and then changes to a higher constant value for the next <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> seconds.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The kinetic energy of the object remains constant for the first <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4\"><math alttext=\"4\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>4</mn></math></span></span> seconds and then changes to a lower constant value for the next <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> seconds.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The kinetic energy of the object remains constant for the first <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4\"><math alttext=\"4\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>4</mn></math></span></span> seconds and then decreases to zero over the next <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> seconds.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
